tweets.text:
My mom is down in Fl, she is from Hawai'i, she knows allllll about storms.

She always parks her car on a low lying area just in case it floods, it will get totaled so she can get a new car.

It has worked once! https://t.co/P5L2siGB0C

Today's hopeful trends in the model tracks (from South Florida's perspective) have led NHC to adjust the "cone of concern". Still a high confidence forecast into the northern #Bahamas (be ready!) but then a northbound turn. Miami is still in the cone and we need to monitor, still https://t.co/3kw5l5byZZ
